### Installation
Loading indicator is released as a npm package, so you can install it with 

    npm install react-loading-indicator --save

### Usage
Include LoadingIndicator and put it somewhere in the top-component. For example:

    import LoadingIndicator from "react-loading-indicator";

    var Layout = React.createClass({
        render: function() {
            return (
                <div className="layout">
                    <LoadingIndicator/>
                </div>
            );
        }
    });

Now, whenever you need to show an indicator, trigger `loader.show`, for example:


    loadPage: function() {
        $(window).trigger("loader.show");
        // do your ajax thing.
    },

    loadPageCallback: function() {
        $(window).trigger("loader.hide");
    }


### Styling


    .loader-60devs .loader-60devs-progress {
        background: #ff6f00;
    }


